Objective
=========

WikiGram aims to compute the most used trigrams in the Wikipedia articles.


How to start WikiGram?
======================

Build WikiGram
--------------

* Install Maven (http://maven.apache.org/). Debian example:
aptitude install maven2

* Build the jar : run Maven in the root directory of the project (the directory containing the file 'pom.xml'):
mvn package


Download a Wikipedia dump
-------------------------

* The dumps are downloadable at http://dumps.wikimedia.org/. For example:
wget http://dumps.wikimedia.org/frwiki/20111214/frwiki-20111214-pages-articles.xml.bz2


Start WikiGram
--------------

* Set the M2_REPO environment variable to Maven repository if necessary. For example:
M2_REPO="/home/me/.m2/repository"

* Run the script, give the dump as parameter. For example:
./wikigram.sh frwiki-20111214-pages-articles.xml.bz2


